Date: Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] networking: wire RequestJournal into the NetworkService layer

Connects the RequestJournal (src/journal/request_journal.cc) to
Chromium's NetworkService as a URLLoaderInterceptor. Every outbound
HTTP/HTTPS request passes through RecordRequest(); every response
passes through RecordResponse().

Integration points:
  1. NetworkServiceImpl::CreateURLLoaderFactory — installs the interceptor
  2. URLLoaderClient bridge — forwards response headers + body size
  3. BrowserContext::GetRequestJournal() — accessor for the per-profile
     journal instance (created in profile_impl.cc)

The Journal is intentionally non-blocking: it classifies and records
async on its SQLite task runner while the request proceeds immediately.
Classification errors never block a request.

PILLAR: Transparency
JOURNAL: This patch IS the journal — it wires every request into the
         Request Journal SQLite store and fires observer notifications
         to the sidebar panel in real time.

